Done. Here's a summary of what was done:

---

**BUG-023 — DialogTitle a11y warning**

Root cause: The custom `DialogTitle` in `ui/dialog.tsx` renders a plain `<h2>` — not `DialogPrimitive.Title`. Radix's `DialogContent` wraps `DialogPrimitive.Content`, which uses React context to check at mount whether a `DialogPrimitive.Title` has registered itself. A plain `<h2>` is invisible to this check, so the console.error fires regardless of visual title presence.

Fix: In `canvas-view.tsx`, import `* as DialogPrimitive from "@radix-ui/react-dialog"` and use `<DialogPrimitive.Title className="...">` directly (styled to match the existing visual). Added a comment documenting the root cause and that `section-detail-panel.tsx` has the same issue (read-only, not fixable in this task).

**IMP-036 — Starters hidden on DB error**

Restructured the `loadingTemplates ? ... : templateError ? ... : ...` ternary into a two-branch form: loading=skeletons; non-loading=grid. Inside the grid: error message appears at top (conditional), DB templates hidden on error, starters always render. Empty state only shown when no error and both lists are empty.

**IMP-030 — Icon button aria-labels**

Audited both owned files. All icon-only buttons already had `aria-label`: Templates (`"Browse templates"`), Color (`"Toggle coloring rules"`), Delete template (`"Delete template"`), Close tab (`"Close ${tab.name} tab"`), Add tab (`"Add new tab"`). No changes needed.

**Verification:** TypeScript clean (0 errors), lint clean (0 errors, 1 pre-existing warning in unowned file).
